Center: Centre for Photonuclear Experiments Data, Moscow State University, Russia
title: Nuclear photoeffect on three-particle nuclei.

x4freetext: Nuclear photoeffect on three-particle nuclei.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Zhurnal Eksperimental`noi i Teoret. Fiziki, Vol.47, p.30 (1964)
Jour: Journal of Experimental and Theoretical Physics, Vol.20, p.20 (1965)

x4freetext: English translation of ZET,47,30,1964.
The cloud  chamber  filled  with  He-3  gas  with   a
pressure  of  0.9  atm  was  used  simultaneously as
detector and  target.  The  purity  of He-3 used was
better than 99.99%  and the concentration of tritium
did not exceed 10**(-11)%.
The cloud chamber 30 cm in diam.  and 8  cm  in
height placed into 10400 Oe magnetic field  operated
in a collimated  bremsstrahlung  beam  with  maximum
energy 170 MeV.
The characteristic  peculiarities  of  the  reactions
He-3(g,p)D-2 and He-3(g,np)2p permitted  the  unique
identification    of    these   processes   in   the
overwhelming majority of cases even by scanning  the
cloud chamber photographs visually
Kinematically determined.
Statistical errors.
The  error  connected   with   the  intensity
measurement is about of 6%.
Data for    reaction   He-3(g,p)H-2   cross   section
presented on Fig.  2 were published in  the  SUBENTs
Data for reaction He-3(g,n)2p cross section presented
on Fig. 4 were published in the SUBENT M0479005.
Data were compiled at the Russia MSU SINP
CDFE by V.Varlamov.
